title: MENA Golf Tour: Four golfers tied for lead
text:
MENA Golf Tour: Four golfers tied for lead Ben Alexander October 20, 2015 
Young amateur Ben Alexander shot a career-best five-under 67 to join Stuart Archibald, Christofer Blomstrand and Cyril Suk atop the leaderboard on the opening day of the Muscat Hills Golf Citizen Championship on Monday. 
The 21 year old Scot rebounded from an early bogey on the first with two birdies on the front nine and picked up three more shots coming home, including an eagle on the par-five on 13th, to introduce himself on the MENA Golf Tour after missing the cut in all his six previous outings. 
England’s Archibald and Sweden’s Blomstrand went bogey-free at the Muscat Hills Golf & Country Club, while Czech Republic's Suk, who won the 2014 Sheikh Maktoum Dubai Open, reeled off four birdies in his last seven holes to move into a four-way tie for the lead. 
Sweden’s Per Barth, the winner of the Sheikh Maktoum Dubai Open last month, was placed solo fifth, a shot adrift. A group of ten players were at three-under 69. On a hot and humid day when 30 players broke par, Morocco’s Younes El Hassani and Mustapha El Maouas carded matching three-under 69s for a share of the lead in the MENA division, one shot clear of their compatriots Mohamed Belaroussia and Mehdi Saissi. 
Also, India’s 15 year old Rayhan Thomas returned a two-under 70, highlighted by an eagle on the 13th, to occupy solo second in the amateur division behind Alexander. 
For the hosts, Azaan al Rumhy carded a disappointing nine over par for 81 to be placed tenth in the amateur category that comprises 11 players. 
Oman's other golfer, Ali Hameed, decided to withdraw at the last-minute. He told Muscat Daily, “I wanted to focus on the forthcoming Nomura Cup in Abu Dhabi, UAE that begins on Thursday.” Similar content
